                            To seize the massive reach of this popular social networking channel, MCGI has launched these fan pages to provide users with relevant updates about MCGI, its leaders, and its programs:
                            <LineBreak />- Facebook.com/BroEliseoSoriano
                            <LineBreak />- Facebook.com/KuyaDanielRazon
                            <LineBreak />- Facebook.com/AngDatingDaanTV
                            <LineBreak />- Facebook.com/TheOldPath
                            </TextBlock>

                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageSubHeaderTitle}">Twitter</TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            <Bold>@BroEliSoriano</Bold><LineBreak />
                            Follow Bro. Eli for answers to questions about faith, not to mention, scripturally-inspired tweets.
                            </TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            <Bold>@AngDatingDaanTV, @TheOldPathTV</Bold><LineBreak />
                            Besides giving the freshest Church news and event announcements, these Twitter accounts make up-to-the-minute tweets in Filipino and English respectively, during Worldwide Bible Expositions.
                            </TextBlock>
                        </StackPanel>
                    </ScrollViewer>
                </DataTemplate>
            </HubSection>

            <HubSection Name="ItemPageSectionFive">
                <DataTemplate>
                    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
                        <StackPanel>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageHeaderTitle}">Satellite</TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            Satellite technology has offered to humanity the gift of worldwide communication. Aside its functions supporting global positioning, weather forecasting, and others, it is most useful in television and radio broadcasting, where news is delivered from one point of the globe to another. This technology has proven to be an effective means in delivering information regardless of distance and difference in time, therefore Members Church of God International leaders, Bro.Eli and Bro.Daniel, decided to put it to good use.
                            </TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            Subsequent to being based overseas, Bro. Eli used to travel from one city or state to another, to preach the unadulterated doctrines of Christ to other nationalities. But after realizing that this has taken a lot of his time, the International Evangelist along with Bro Daniel realized they had to think of a measure that will both be time-saving and efficient. Satellite broadcasting was the best option.
                            </TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            Knowing there are people who had been in constant search for biblical truths, Bro. Eli was encouraged to take his chances in spite of the fact that the cost of leasing this technology is expensive. Bro. Daniel Razon, the Vice Presiding Minister, and incidentally a Mass Communications Specialist shored up all the support he could muster for Bro. Eli.
                            </TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            Starting with NSS 806 covering North, Central and South of the Americas, Europe and North Africa, the MCGI leaders had braved to test the waters. After receiving a decent number of viewership, Bro.Eli and Bro.Daniel decided to expand The Old Path's propagation reach through several other satellites that will increase the reach of the global propagation efforts of the Church of God.
                            </TextBlock>
                            <TextBlock Style="{ThemeResource ItemPageContent}">
                            As MCGI's satellite broadcast started to reach more nations around the world, it became inevitable for The Old Path television program that started in the Philippines to be replicated in non-English formats, including El Camino Antiguo for Spanish-speaking people, and the O Caminho Antigo program for the Portuguese-speaking populace.
                            </TextBlock>
                        </StackPanel>
                    </ScrollViewer>
                </DataTemplate>
            </HubSection>

